Quarantined at our homes, we usually forget to take care of our skin. Resulting in dull and tired skin.

I recently came across @the_body_avenue skincare products, tried them and thought of sharing with you guys as well.

1. The Body Avenue Unisex Charcoal peel off mask- This charcoal enriched easy peel off mask detoxifies skin and unclogs pores, which helps in making the skin clearer, brighter and draws out toxins and impurities.
I tried this myself and you guys can clearly see the results after peeling the mask off. My blackheads also got removed.

The best part about this peel off mask is, it is unisex. Anyone and everyone can use this to get clearer skin.

2. The Body Avenue Rose facial toner- After peeling off the mask, it is necessary to minimize the open pores. This toner helps tighten the pores, hydrates the skin, and makes the skin look fresher. Totally loved its effect on my face.

These products are easily available on @amazondotin
And are worth spending on. 💫🥰

My week in Singapore 🇸🇬 ❤️

(Travel, vacation, Singapore trip, vacation outfits)

My complete Bridal entry, just how I had always imagined ❤️

I entered with Phoolon ki chaadar, the four pillars of which were held by my brothers, showing their immense love and support towards me, just like they have shown in my life ❤️

The first phase of my entry had the whole bride side dancing on Dhol, because I also wanted to feel the baraat entry- enjoying and dancing my way into the most special day of my life ❤️

The second phase had all my bridesmaids and sisters lined up and making way for me, through flower shower. Showing their love and blessings for my new journey ❤️

The third phase was me walking hand in hand with my parents. Because without them, every happiness is incomplete. They are my strength, and I wanted everyone to know, I’ll always be their little girl, always walking hand in hand with them. ❤️

The fourth and last phase of my bridal entry was me walking the aisle, towards the new beginning, my love waiting for me at the other side. I didn’t want to enter on any sad bridal song. All I wanted in this special walk was to dedicate my love and feelings to him. And this song was just perfect ❤️

Shot & edited by- @lightstrokesphotography 

( Bride entry, Bridal walk, Destination wedding)
Us, sun, sand and sea, that sounds like a perfect summer to me ❤️🌊🏖️☀️👫🏻
